<hl>
<seg id=1> Discriminated against by the natives, hundreds of English immigrants left Australia. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> French News Agency, Sidney According to an investigation yesterday, because of the sense of "being hostile to Britain" and discrimination by the natives, hundreds of English immigrants decided to leave Australia. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> For the benefit of the local immigrants as well as the Australian economy, the British Immigrants Association called on the government to pay attention to the problem. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Chairman of the Association Hunt pointed out that the British people thought that the Australians were hostile to them, and the Australian economy "might lose thousands of dollars every year because of this." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> He said that it's really disappointing that so many British people wanted to leave Australia because almost all of them were economically independent technicians. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> He told the reporters that: "According to the immigration rules, these immigrants are not those you want to get rid of. " </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> British people made up 14% of the Australian immigrants. </seg>
<seg id=8> However, according to the figures from the Immigration Department, although 11,978 British people emigrated to Australia from 1996 to 1997, 3737 people left. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> Hunt said that the Association made an investigation in Melbourne, and a quarter of the British people believed that they had received discrimination. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> Almost 40% of the interviewees thought that the local people showed partiality to non-British people. </seg>
<seg id=11> 37% of them pointed out that the British people's cases were not treated the same as the others. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> About 35% of them complained that the media was chief criminal for the local people's prejudices towards the British immigrants. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=13> Hunt said that the anti-British attitude of the former Prime Minister of Australia Shrine didn't play a good role in it. </seg>
</p>
